<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-201-119 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 439 977</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  March 13 1991 n1631* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Minigrams.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT/><TEXT>MINIGRAMSandM;IBM is jogging the arms of Wall Street analysts, hinting firmly that some ofthem have got carried away in their enthusiasm for its RS/6000 business: somehave been projecting sales this year as high as $3,000m, three times the 1990figure, but IBM is signalling that $1,700m to $2,000m would be safer.andM;- o -andM;Overall, analysts are feeling much less confident about IBM's business thisyear, with Daniel Mandresh at Merrill Lynch andamp; Co cutting his 1991 forecast to$10.90 a share from $11.25, compared with 1990's $10.51 a share; he alsoforecasts that IBM will see a &quot;down&quot; quarter for the period to the end ofthis month.andM;- o -andM;Unisys Corp is expected to give its defence systems arm a separate board inwhat is seen as preparation for sale of the business: it may also seek toliquidate the assets of its Unisys Finance Corp, which leases its productsand has $684m of debt that is carried on the parent company's books; thetotal debt at Unisys amounts to some $3,500m; Unisys intends to retain theunit but lay off the financing with banks and insurance companies.andM;- o -andM;Cray Electronics Plc says it has raised #2.08m from the sale of the assetsand some liabilities of its Lloyd Instruments Ltd subsidiary.andM;- o -andM;The Object Management Group in Framingham, Massachusetts has issued a RequestFor Information for an Object Model, a formal description of the allowablebehaviour and visible characteristics of objects within an object-orientedenvironment, saying it wants a common description of an object that canbecome standard across very type of computer in use; the Object Model willdescribe what an object is, what it can do, and how it interacts with otherobjects and the club wants comments from developers of object-orientedproducts; the Object Model will become a consistent reference to ensureinteroperability and design uniformity within the Group's ObjectManagementArchitecture components; responses to the Request must be in by May1.andM;- o -andM;ATandamp;T Co has written to &quot;several hundred&quot; of the employees of its computersystems division advising them that if they can't find positions with otherunits of ATandamp;T they will be laid off at the end of May on terms unlikely to begenerous.andM;- o -andM;Fujitsu Ltd says that the formation of the new Fulcrum Communications Ltd outof the manufacturing side of the British Telecommunications Plc company inBirmingham will involve initial investment of #18m.andM;- o -andM;When British Telecommunications Plc wants to conceal the value of atransaction while giving the appearance of being helpful, it says that thedeal involves &quot;less than 1%&quot; of net assets: the formula currently translatesas under #140m.andM;- o -andM;Doctus Plc, the Salford, Manchester consultancy group, has sold its tradeinvestment in BNB Resources Plc as part of its programme to reduce gearinglevels: the 9.9% stake was sold at an average of 95 pence per share,producing a profit and proceeds of just under #2m.andM;- o -andM;The Software Publishers Association and the Business Software Alliancegreatly reduce the credibility of their case by quoting telephone numbers forthe &quot;losses&quot; suffered by software companies from illicit use, without takingany account of the way behaviour would alter if pirate users had to pay thefull price for each copy - &quot;oh dear, I guess it's back to the abacus&quot;, butthey do have a cause for grievance over Mexico: they say they support the USgovernment's proposed Free Trade Agreement with Mexico on condition Mexicoimmediately enact a pending copyright bill to provide adequate protection forUS intellectual property - software is presently not explicitly protected,copying for private use is exempt, and the maximum criminal fine forinfringement is a swingeing $3.40!andO;</TEXT></DOC>